# SCSS Conventions

## Color palette — use CSS custom properties

All colors from `_dev/css/custom/base/_colors.scss` are available as CSS vars generated in `_global.scss`:

```scss
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded hex
background: #f7a626;
color: #1e1e1e;
border: 1px solid #c5c5c5;

// ✅ GOOD — CSS custom property from palette
background: var(--clr-yellow);
color: var(--clr-black-3);
border: 1px solid var(--clr-gray-4);
```

Available vars (from `$palette`):
`--clr-white`, `--clr-black`, `--clr-black-2`, `--clr-black-3`,
`--clr-yellow`, `--clr-gray`, `--clr-gray-2`, `--clr-gray-3`, `--clr-gray-4`,
`--clr-green`, `--clr-green-2`

Never hardcode a hex that exists in the palette. If a color is not in the palette, leave it as hex or add it to `$palette` first.

## BEM nesting — use `&` for elements and modifiers

```scss
// ❌ BAD — flat CSS-style selectors
.block { ... }
.block__element { ... }
.block__element--modifier { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — nested SCSS with &
.block {
  ...
  &__element {
    ...
    &--modifier { ... }
  }
}
```

## File structure

- Each section partial starts with `@use "../base" as *;` and `@use "../utils" as *;`.
- Group responsive overrides at the bottom inside `@include md(...)` blocks, nesting with `&` where applicable.

## Typography

Prefer design tokens as mixins in `_dev/css/custom/utils/_mixins.scss` — see [`scss-typography-mixins.mdc`](scss-typography-mixins.mdc).
